🚀 Day 15 of 30 Days SQL Challenge

Today’s focus was understanding GROUP BY deeply — and applying it to Problem 619 on LeetCode (Biggest Single Number).



 Find the largest number that appears only once in the table.

Key idea:

Group numbers using GROUP BY

Filter numbers that appear once using HAVING COUNT(*) = 1

Use MAX() to get the biggest among them





SELECT MAX(num) AS num

FROM (

    SELECT num

    FROM MyNumbers

    GROUP BY num

    HAVING COUNT(*) = 1

) AS single_numbers;



💡 Today’s Learning:

 Understanding why we use GROUP BY makes solving problems much easier.

